Program: The Forum
Title: 01/01/2012 GMT
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00mgpny
Last Broadcast Date: New Year's Day 2012
This week we bring you the thoughts of four outstanding young people on what the future might hold for us: Winston Damarillo, a software entrepreneur from the Philippines, who believes cloud computing can transform developing countries; Canadian criminologist Baillie Aaron and her new ideas for helping young offenders; Ben Green, a brilliant young Cambridge mathematician, who is seeking to unearth new secrets about prime numbers; and Fauzia Musa, Indian-born trend analyst, who scours the world of commerce, fashion and travel for signs of changing attitudes. Illustration by Emily Kasriel; Young people's ideas - Primes, trends, clouds and prisoners Show less